<section>
  <h2 id="javascript">JavaScript</h2>

  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">Basics (<strong>Types</strong>, <strong>Operators</strong>, <strong>Control Structures</strong>, etc.)</li>
    <li class="fragment">Object Oriented Programming (<strong>Objects</strong>, <strong>Prototypes</strong>)</li>
    <li class="fragment">Functional Programming (<strong>Functions</strong> as <em>First Class Objects</em>)</li>
    <li class="fragment">Patterns (<strong>Encapsulation</strong>, <strong>Namespacing</strong>, <strong>Interfaces</strong>, etc.)</li>
  </ul>

  <aside class="notes">
* Who already knows js?
* Describe - type system, tools for abstraction... like inheritance,
</aside>
</section>

<section>

  <h2 id="server-side-programming">Server Side Programming</h2>

  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">Server Side Framework/Language - <strong>Node.js</strong></li>
    <li class="fragment">HTTP</li>
    <li class="fragment">Web Framework - <strong>Express</strong></li>
    <li class="fragment">Session Management</li>
    <li class="fragment">Building and Consuming APIs</li>
    <li class="fragment">Forms</li>
    <li class="fragment">MVC</li>
    <li class="fragment">Deployment</li>
  </ul>

  <aside class="notes">
* Request Methods / Response Codes?
* What's MVC stand for? Examples?
</aside>
</section>

<section>

  <h2 id="storing-data">Storing Data</h2>

  <ul>
    <li class="fragment">NoSQL Database - <strong>MongoDB</strong> (<a href="http://db-engines.com/en/ranking">btw, database rankings!</a>)</li>
    <li class="fragment">Database Design</li>
    <li class="fragment">Using a Database Abstraction Layer - <strong>Mongoose</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <aside class="notes">
* has anyone use NoSQL data stores?
* what about traditional databases? Postgres? MySQL?
* some [comparisons](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/sqlite-vs-mysql-vs-postgresql-a-comparison-of-relational-database-management-systems)
* Hooooowzzzz about JSON?
</aside>
</section>

<section>
  <h2 id="client-side-build-out">Client Side <em>Build-Out</em></h2>

