<section>
  <h2 id="motivation-for-technologies">Motivation for Technologies</h2>

  <p><strong>Why use JavaScript, Node.js and Express over Ruby and Ruby on Rails or Python and Django?</strong></p>

  <p>The concepts and theory remain roughly the same across all of these <em>technology stacks</em>, but here&#39;s why I chose what I did:</p>

  <ol>
    <li class="fragment">we only need to learn one language throughout the course for server side development, front end development&#8230; and even for querying the database</li>
    <li class="fragment">pretty straightforward to install the entire stack (node, mongodb) on Windows, Linux and OSX</li>
    <li class="fragment">seems like there&#39;s a lot of opportunity out there (I&#39;ve had former students contact me to let me know that they&#39;re working with node professionally!)</li>
    <li class="fragment">work with tools that are either currently or becoming industry standards (<strong>git</strong>, <strong>jshint</strong>, etc.)</li>
    <li class="fragment">a <strong>fun</strong> stack to learn (really! &#8230;I&#39;m excited about delving into it too!)</li>
    <li class="fragment">we&#39;ll talk about the technical trade-offs for using this stack next week</li>
  </ol>
</section>

